Avoid importing wx when --ignore-gooey is part of the command line arguments.

wx has dependencies on graphical libraries and servers. Importing it on
a headless machines causes the scripts to fail.

This change allows gooey-powered scripts to run on headless machines
with the --ignore-gooey option.

Handling of style-oriented ascii espace sequences.

Using the RichTextCtrl widget we are able to use advanced formatting in the console pannel. The formatting information is extracted from the text stream by searching for terminal escape sequences. The sequence values are taken from the colored package, which becomes a lazy dependency (imported only when the feature is activated).

The previous implementation (using the TextCtrl widget) has been extracted into a separate class.

The client code chooses between the basic or the rich class based on the richtext_controls configuration parameter. The default is to use the previous implementation based on TextCtrl.

commit_message:
Remove leftover reference to `type_arg_widget`.

argparse_to_json.py:

    return supplied_widget or type_arg_widget or default
closes #100 - decorator not correctly handling arguments
closes #399 - missing translation of default groups (+ correcting subgroup layouts)

Fix Hebrew translations

References #411. Move changes from "master" to "1.0.3-release" branch.
Fix crash when no default on listbox
closes #408 - allow hiding of widgets in UI
updated README and added gooey_options docs

Update Gooey_options

Be explicit about widget, otherwise it's confusing.

Some styling
fix rich console was not appending - fix #433

change consts used for style

Based on
https://wxpython.org/Phoenix/docs/html/wx.richtext.RichTextCtrl.html#wx.richtext.RichTextCtrl
the style constants used are wrong.

Fix text wrapping in 1.0.3-release

This fixes the problem reported in https://github.com/chriskiehl/Gooey/issues/463
use i18n in a less verbose way
Add support for wildcards, message, defualtFile, DefaultDir and DefaultPath for Choosers
Update options to snake_case instead of CamelCase and add it to documentation

detect URLs in rich console and make them clickable

closes #421

Also closes #427 Auto-URL is confused by wide characters
corrected (more polite ;-)) and completed Dutch translation
add explicity wx imports to enable OSX pyinstaller packaging
expose additional top-level API for easier packaging
update Gooey program icon and fix OSX task bar rendering
add .ico and .icns images for cleaner packaging
replace windows program icon with new logo
add option to suppress Gooey's --ignore injection behavior
only add dock image to non win32 runs
hotfix #549 - lock down WX version in setup.py due to breaking changes in latest version

Added Turkish translation

Thanks for the great app.
Updated Bosnian language file to match the current English file

Improved the iter_parsers function of the argparse_to_json.py to allow
the extraction to the sub parser recursively
closes #515 - fix typo in doc string
update README to reference new .png override requirement

Revert "Improved the iter_parsers function of the argparse_to_json.py to allow"

This reverts commit 4140f8e8e69585d1a421757d1fc1944b6de6bf36.

Added a cast to string for the Dropdown default and choices values.

This allows using any printable object as choices list (some kings of Enums for instance), which is allowed by argparse but not by wxPython.
Changed the check on TextContainer default values to allow False-evaluated defaults.
closes #527 - add documentation for richtext controls
Closes #200 substitute command line arguments for defaults
pass footer_bg_color from buildSpec to Footer

Fix Issue 553: Handle Windows volume labels correctly in MultiDirChooser.

If running on a Windows system, strips volume labels from directory path to leave only the drive letter. This path can then be ingested by other functionality that expects valid paths.
Substitute Python3-only code for Python 2.7-compatible code.

Fix Issue 550: MultiDirChooser cannot handle paths with spaces

Instead of using the general formatter, use formatters.multiFileChooser, which handles paths with spaces.

Include MultiDirChooser in the list of Choosers

Remove MultiFileSaver, which does not exist.

Issue 554: Fix MultiFileChooser output formatting.

Also adds MultiFileChooser to __ALL__.

Includes tests for formatters.multiFileChooser.

Other choosers may need similar fixes; I have not experimented with them.

Pre-fill counter dropdowns with 0 (not 1) to 10 inclusive.
Fixes issue #569.
closes #517 - radio group not enabling widget when initial_selection is set
closes #497 - fix show_header_title not corretly setting visibility
closes #480 - program_description not overriding parser description

ProcessController.py (run): Use default Popen buffer size to
avoid Python 3.8 runtime warnings:

  "RuntimeWarning: line buffering (buffering=1) isn't supported in binary
   mode, the default buffer size will be used"
closes #496 - add option to start Gooey in fullscreen mode
closes #469 - prevent argparse ==SUPPRESS== from showing in Gooey
closes #500 - nargs with default values being mapped incorrectly
closes #593 & #591 - dynamic updates causes slowdowns and loses selection

Prevent crash when getting dynamic properties

Since `args` is a string, the `Popen` constructor interprets "/usr/bin/python myscript.py" as a path to an executable instead of "/usr/bin/python" with argument "myscript.py".
Adding `shell=True` makes this behave as expected.

Fix #584
Copy widgets and their configuration from parent parsers. Resolves #608
Added test for parent inheritance behaviour and made "widgets" behave the same as "defaults" for duplicate named arguments.
Resolve all wx warnings and errors and bump version to 4.1.0

Fix show_stop_warning

Previously, show_stop_warning=False would make the stop button do nothing
Now, if show_stop_warning=False the stop button stops the program without a warning dialog
add test cases for show_stop_warning decorator option

Do not translate arguments in add_subparsers

add_subparsers is typically called before Gooey initialization, when
translations are not loaded.
closes #592 - clicking close button can cause Gooey to hang
add missing return statement in processor.py
allow control+scrollwheel to zoom rich text console #432

Ensure OnDropFiles function matches interface

Fixes the following error printed to the console after dropping a file onto a text box: 
TypeError: invalid result from FileDrop.OnDropFiles(), a 'bool' is expected not 'NoneType'

Update french.json

I translated all the missing phrases from the english.json file.  I have checked that it remains valid json afterwards. (no missing commas etc).
closes #625 - terminal font and colors not being set correctly
Add Listbox height option to documentation
fixes weird bug in RadioGroup where child interactions could cause radiobuttons to lose their selection
Use program_name instead of script file name in macOS menu
Fix implicit float to int conversion raising DeprecationWarning
closes #645 - drag-and-drop doesn't honor multiFileChooser logic
